    {
      "id": "QFRd62UQhFGafNCw4Q-YH",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3357.5835421046268,
      "y": -695.8994203118905,
      "width": 2006.3101806640625,
      "height": 1068.8461538461536,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b4I",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 205563971,
      "version": 3647,
      "versionNonce": 2045366318,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774922342871,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\nBatch DCR - Covers the high-volume HCO DCR processing system that:\n\n  -Receives files from SWIFT on fixed dates monthly\n  -Uses different CSV templates for different DCR types\n  -Auto-approves after offline third-party validation (unless duplicates found)\n  -Requires processing 5,000-6,000 records per file within a specified timeframe\n\nCreate DCR Match & Merge - Describes the deduplication logic using:\n\n  -SCDF for batch deduplication via Elasticsearch\n  -EBX Match plugin for non-batch scoring\n  -Notes the sync risk between ES and core layer\n\nBatch Review - Identifies workflow gaps where:\n\n  -External data stewards validate HCP DCRs daily offline\n  -Current design requires all DCRs validated before batch submission\n  -Proposed optimization allows partial batch submission and processes validated records immediately\n\n",
      "fontSize": 40.71794871794871,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\nBatch DCR - Covers the high-volume HCO DCR processing system that:\n\n  -Receives files from SWIFT on fixed dates monthly\n  -Uses different CSV templates for different DCR types\n  -Auto-approves after offline third-party validation (unless duplicates found)\n  -Requires processing 5,000-6,000 records per file within a specified timeframe\n\nCreate DCR Match & Merge - Describes the deduplication logic using:\n\n  -SCDF for batch deduplication via Elasticsearch\n  -EBX Match plugin for non-batch scoring\n  -Notes the sync risk between ES and core layer\n\nBatch Review - Identifies workflow gaps where:\n\n  -External data stewards validate HCP DCRs daily offline\n  -Current design requires all DCRs validated before batch submission\n  -Proposed optimization allows partial batch submission and processes validated records immediately\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
